<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">I got a little carried away so this is longer than i ment, <br>
but Bottom line is Magicians can Solo (and do)... <br>
below explains my reasoning and some tactics that worked for me so far.<p>

First, If no one wants them in a group then all of those 45+ lvl Magicians must have soloed... thus contradicting your statement that they can't.<p>

I am a 7th lvl (less than 2wks to reach that lvl), High Elf, MagicUser (1/2 bubble from 8) and I can say from exp. that I soloed from lvl 1 and others were asking to join with me after lvl 4.  Granted they were only 8-12 lvl themself, but I ran around with them a few times because I liked someone to chat with not because I needed their help. If they had to leave I went right on adventuring.<p>

At level 4 you get GATE so if you manage your mana you can always get out of a bad situation. Also you can buy Elemental spells from your Guild and cast them at lvl 4 on.  I mostly use a Fire Elemental because when he hits, he does damage...when MOB hits him, he does damage ... (the key to pet for me is buy at least 10-30 Malichite for about 5sp each, depending on CHAR and Faction standing, from merchant in cities) and just keep replacing pet (stand far enough back you have time to get spell off) when he/she gets killed. Use programmed HotKeys for ATTACK,GUARD,STATS and BACKOFF and you wont loose your pet so often because he heals faster than you do. You MED, he WHACKS, you monitor his status and back him off when he gets low, he restores his HP, he WHACKS some more.  Its all about pet management. <p>

High Elves see in dark (infravision), but can cast Wisp stone for light if you cant, create food,water, but more important bandages.<br>
Last night I applied bandages (will restore up to 50% hp) to a 19th Lvl Fighter that didnt even know he could bind wounds himself.  I produce the bandage and either sell or give (depending on your inclination, and believe me a fighter with less than 1 bubble of hp sitting in a zone away from a city with no cleric will be happy to pay for your bandaging).  <p>

On the subject of money... Learn a skill - I put some Training into Tailoring and bought the Tailoring Book and a Large Sewing kit. ( I think you have to have the book with you, but not sure ... just had more success with the book...you dont have to hold it, I just keep mine in a backpack on me )<br>
 Combine 2 spider (not spiderling) silks in kit to make a silk swatch.<br>
 1 Silk Swatch combined with pattern (also about 5sp) to make silk armor. <br>
 You can do the same with ruined wolf for patched armor, but magic users cant wear (can sell or trade though)<p>

At lvl 8 you get invisbility and create staff so you can always create weapon to give it to your pet, so that he/she does even more damage (speaking of which, If you pick up rusty swords and maces you cant use, give it to your pet so he doesnt get killed so easily) ... well thats it for now, hope I said something you could use, but if not remember, its a game, its supposed to be fun....</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
